exampleTwo	"This is to test painting with a gray tone. It also tests that the seaming	with gray patterns is correct in the microcode. Lets you paint for a	while and then automatically stops. This only works at Depth of 1."	"create a small black Form source as a brush."	| _gsSqueakTemp_f _gsSqueakTemp_aBitBlt _gsSqueakTemp_displayDepth |	_gsSqueakTemp_displayDepth := Display depth.	Display newDepth: 1.	_gsSqueakTemp_f := Form extent: 20 @ 20.	_gsSqueakTemp_f fillBlack.	"create a BitBlt which will OR gray into the display."	_gsSqueakTemp_aBitBlt := BitBlt				destForm: Display				sourceForm: _gsSqueakTemp_f				fillColor: Color gray				combinationRule: Form over				destOrigin: Sensor cursorPoint				sourceOrigin: 0 @ 0				extent: _gsSqueakTemp_f extent				clipRect: Display computeBoundingBox.	"paint the gray Form on the screen for a while."	[Sensor anyButtonPressed]		whileFalse: [_gsSqueakTemp_aBitBlt destOrigin: Sensor cursorPoint.			_gsSqueakTemp_aBitBlt copyBits].	Display newDepth: _gsSqueakTemp_displayDepth